lead_paragraph: Charley Hoffman remained one stroke clear after the weather-hit second round of the Houston Open on Friday, despite bogeying his final hole, while Jordan Spieth endured a frustrating day to finish six shots off the pace.

headline.print_headline: Hoffman One Ahead in Houston, Spieth Six Back
